Use this picker to choose the best hands from the batch. If no good options are present, change the seed in the detailer and try again.

You will have to cancel the queued generation once the batch is done and load it from the history to pick a specific result to use. From there, click queue prompt again to resume with the fixed hand applied to the image.
I found this handfix workflow on reddit while looking up info on the MeshGraphormer Hand Refiner node. I do not take credit for it.

This node below seems to no longer work as intended in this workflow. For now I am bypassing it.

The way it is supposed to work:

Use this picker to select only some of the hands if you need. For example, if one hand is okay or if you have multiple people.

This watermark removal workflow is not my creation. I found it on civitai while looking for watermark detectors for the detailer node.

The workflow has been tweaked so that the detection threshold can be adjusted further than the original workflow allowed.

The detection threshold may need to be adjusted depending on if it is giving a false detection or if it is not detecting watermarks on your image. It is not super precise, but I have had good results. In some cases, I have had to go as low as 0.001 for it to detect small watermarks.
This switch just allows for toggling on and off Baked VAE if your checkpoint has it.

The reason I am using this node is because civitai does not appear to be able to pull the resource data from the image when using the "Post Image" function.

After being asked enough times if my image uses a specific lora, I decided to make use of this node. Using this node along with the Inspire Pack nodes I am using for prompts, all model, lora, embedding, etc. information is now readable by civitai. It does not work with using a multi-model merge in the workflow in my experience. This is probably just a limitation of the node.
I set up USDU this way while experimenting. It seemed to get better results for me, but could just be wishful thinking.
